title: Seahawks' Jackson unhurt in car accident
text:

SEATTLE (KING) -- Seattle Seahawks RB Fred Jackson was not hurt when he crashed his Corvette near the Seahawks training facility Tuesday afternoon. 
Renton Police said officers responded to the intersection of Seahawks Way and Lake Washington Boulevard North for a report of a one car collision. 
Officers determined that at about 4:49 p.m., a 2016 Chevrolet Corvette lost control as it drove southbound on Seahawks Way, struck a street sign, and came to rest on the north side of Lake Washington Boulevard North. The car sustained moderate front end damage. 
Jackson appeared uninjured but was taken to the Seahawks facility so team personnel could evaluate him, police said. 
Police said there was no evidence that Jackson was racing, as had been reported by TMZ. 
Police said Jackson remained on scene until officers could speak to him and was "polite and cooperative." 
The accident comes the same day the Seahawks re-activated fullback Derrick Coleman to the 53-man roster after he was suspended last week following an alleged hit and run in Bellevue. 
He's under investigation for vehicular assault and felony hit and run but prosecutors say it could be several weeks before a decision on charges.
